(2465)-Nicolai, E (2225) NED-chT 0506 2005 (9.5) 1-0} {Despite the fact that
this move worked very well in the game, Black's play could be improved with}
Bg4 $5 {when White's development would be harder compared to the game.}) 8...
Nb4 (8... Nf6 9. Nf3 Nbd7 10. c6 bxc6 11. Be2 {transposes to 7...Nf6.}) 9. a3 {
This position was reached in two games. Now} N4c6 $1 $146 {[%cal Gb8d7,Gc8e6,
Gc6d4] is a nice improvement, but a little counterintuitive. Instead of
