Bxg7 Kxg7 14. h4 $1 $40 {transposes to the notes of 7...Nc6.}) (11... Qc4 12.
O-O Qxc5 $2 {is also bad in view of} 13. Nd5 $1 $18) 12. Bh6 $1 Be6 13. Bxg7
Kxg7 {Bivol,A (2368)-Padmini,R (2345) Wch Rapid (Women) 2021 (3) 0-1} {Here
White could have consolidated her advantage by means of the simple} 14. b4 (14.
h4 $1 $40 {also looks good.}) 14... a5 15. O-O Qc4 16. Qb2 $1 Kg8 17. Rab1 $16
{[%csl Ya3,Yb4,Yc5][%cal Gf1c1,Ge2f4] and White keeps a clear pawn up.}) 10.
Be3 $1 {White has a serious lack of development to solve here, but this is the
right move to start dealing with the problem. The bishop stands better on e3
to defend the pawn and to keep an eye on the d4-square, but, more importantly,
it vacates, the d2-square, as we will see.} (10. Nf3 Bg4 $1 {[%cal Gg4f3,Gc6d4,
