1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 g6 3. Nc3 d5 4. cxd5 Nxd5 5. Bd2 Nb6 6. e3 Bg7 {Now let's
examine an interesting alternative which has been seen in recent games:} 7. h4
$5 {an idea introduced by GM Anton Guijarro. Indeed, we do not need further
analysis to immediately recognize that it fits perfectly in the spirit of our
time where rook pawns' advances have proved their value in many openings. The
move looks also very interesting from a practical point of view as the opening
of the h-file should not be underestimated.} e5 {The line is still pretty
fresh (only 16 games!) so it is difficult to determine which is the best
